Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses methods for estimating characteristics of a distribution of interest using Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods, which are probabilistic methods. The paper specifically focuses on convergence diagnostics for MCMC, which are used to determine when it is safe to stop sampling and use the samples to estimate characteristics of the distribution. The paper does not discuss any other sub-categories of AI.
